# STRUCTURAL FEATURE FILTERING INTEGRATION
# ============================================================================
# 
# STRUCTURAL FEATURE SUPPORT DECLARATION:
# - get_supported_structural_features() abstract method in DatasetHandler
# - DFT handler declares support for ALL features (complete quantum data)
# - DMC handler declares LIMITED features (excludes charges, bond lengths)
# - Enables upstream filtering in config_accessors.py
# 
# DFT STRUCTURAL FEATURES:
# - Supports all atom features including partial_charge and mulliken_charge
# - Supports all bond features including bond_length and bond_length_binned
# - Has complete 3D coordinates and quantum chemical data
# - No feature calculation failures expected
# 
# DMC STRUCTURAL FEATURES:
# - Excludes partial_charge (Gasteiger calculation fails)
# - Excludes mulliken_charge (not computed in DMC)
# - Excludes bond_length features (may lack complete 3D coordinates)
# - Conservative feature set prevents NaN/Inf warnings
# 
# BENEFITS:
# - Eliminates NaN/Inf warnings during DMC processing
# - Prevents molecule rejections due to feature extraction failures
# - Provides clear declaration of dataset capabilities
# - Enables automatic feature filtering upstream
# - Zero impact on DFT processing (supports all features)
# 
# INTEGRATION:
# - config_accessors.py queries handler for supported features
# - Configured features automatically filtered by handler capabilities
# - Fallback to legacy behavior if handler query fails
# - Compatible with existing plugin system and transforms
# 
# This implementation provides compliance for structural feature
# filtering while maintaining backward compatibility and all existing
# functionality from migrations.
